ShortName: Profile likelihood
Concepts: Nuisance parameters (needed by a formula but not reported); profiling one parameter out
 by optimising over it (maximise a likelihood, or minimise a fit statistic) at every value of the
 parameter of interest; why the nuisance is re-optimised at each point and the profile reaches the
 same global optimum; the degrees-of-freedom rule — each profiled parameter drops the $\chi^2$ df
 by one; `optimize` as the profiling engine in R
BuildsOn: [likelihood-and-log-likelihood](likelihood-and-log-likelihood/lesson.qmd), [loss-functions-and-optimization](loss-functions-and-optimization/lesson.qmd)
UsedBy: —
